Price decimal precision
There are restrictions to how price can be entered on the order form.
Trying to place an order with a greater number of decimals in the Price field will result in an error and the order will not be created.
  • •
    E.g. Maximum price precision for BTC/USD is 1 decimal. This means that you can place an order for 6500 USD or 6500.1 USD, but not 6500.01 USD.
If the “%” option is used to specify order price, the result will be truncated (rounded down) to the maximum allowed decimal place.
In addition, there are other entry requirements.
Below is a table showing the maximum decimal values for price, as well as the minimum volume amount.
These values can change without notice and are not always current. To view the most up-to-date values, make the following API call:
https://api.kraken.com/0/public/AssetPairs

Why do we limit price precision?

A lower price precision can help order books operate more efficiently by reducing the volume of canceled (unfilled) orders as traders continually jump in front of each other by small fractions in price.
The decimal and thousands separators shown in this article may differ from the formats displayed on our trading platforms. Review our article on how we use points and commas for more information.
